# Copy this file to .env and fill in your details:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# paper-trail loads .env automatically from the working directory at
# startup (internal/envfile) — no third-party dependency, and any value
# already exported in your real shell environment always wins over this
# file.

# Required for lookup/filings/graph/fulltext. SEC EDGAR requires a
# descriptive User-Agent (name + contact email) on every request.
# See https://www.sec.gov/os/accessing-edgar-data
EDGAR_USER_AGENT="Your Name your.email@example.com"

# Required for the ukcharity command only -- the Charity Commission for
# England and Wales's API has no keyless option, unlike every other
# source this tool uses. Register for a free account and subscribe to
# the "Register of Charities" product at
# https://api-portal.charitycommission.gov.uk, then copy both keys from
# your subscription's page (click "Show" next to each). The primary key
# is used first on every request; the secondary is only used as an
# automatic fallback if the primary is rejected (e.g. mid-rotation, or
# it was regenerated and this file hasn't caught up yet) -- set at least
# the primary, the secondary is optional but recommended.
# UK_CHARITY_API_KEY_PRIMARY=
# UK_CHARITY_API_KEY_SECONDARY=

# Reserved for the upcoming sanctions-screening command -- Trade.gov's
# Consolidated Screening List API (OFAC SDN + State/BIS restricted-party
# lists), same Azure API Management setup as the UK Charity Commission
# above (primary/secondary key pair, primary tried first). Sign up for a
# free account at https://developer.trade.gov, subscribe to "Data
# Services Platform APIs" under Products, then copy both keys from your
# Profile page. Not read by any command yet -- the client for this is
# still being built.
# CSL_API_KEY_PRIMARY=
# CSL_API_KEY_SECONDARY=

# Reserved for Phase 2 (OpenCorporates integration). Not read yet.
# OPENCORPORATES_API_KEY=
